column5: It's more of a spring ritual for us than anything else. We had to drag Teagan out because he's not interested in panfish or finicky salmonids, he likes the toothy critters.    A few fish, nice Hawk Air hat    quite a few OOS smallies, a couple sips    My brother had the big score of the day, a quiet moment, tobacco laid and he has a souvenir.    I took this home. I thought it was too beefy to be a deer femur. After looking online, pretty sure it's a deer femur. I'm going to put it in the park by my house after dark to see if it causes a big freak out.    A little butt muncher said he wants to come out next year.

I took this home. I thought it was too beefy to be a deer femur. After looking online, pretty sure it's a deer femur. I'm going to put it in the park by my house after dark to see if it causes a big freak out.      HAHAHA! I can picture the reactions now.  Great day all around!
Your going to see 10 foot chain link fencing around you park within a week .." DESIGNATED ARCHEOLOGICAL DIG SITE"  That bow is super fresh looking. Great catch for your bro
Great report Chris looks like everyone had a great day I am sure Teagan enjoyed it he has a pretty big smile going on and I cant wait to get out in the boat with my grandson Teigan.  Cheers Mitch
Good on ya for laying tobacco down?  Awesome fish, great pics!!!  And lil fisher looks great Chris?
Can you people believe the fish Chris found here???  Unreal
Great day out Chris.  Bones, bows and even babes.
Sweet fish bud! Pike in the creek eh? That's awesome. I'd definitely prefer to hit pike than the trouts.
Nice report Chris!  Can't wait to see next years report with the little butt muncher!!  Your cat looks pretty excited about the bone..

You gotta love cottage country. Paddling up to the Beer Store for some brown trout.  Lil Fisher isn't speaking very clearly yet, but I could barely make out what I think were the words "Rick", and what sounded like "funny guy". Weird.
